      <h2 style="text-align:center;">St Helens Has Some of the Strongest ECO4 Grant Eligibility in Merseyside</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Two factors combine to make St Helens one of the areas where ECO4 grants have the most impact. First, St Helens is specifically identified as an ECO4 priority area. Second, the borough has more back boilers per property than almost anywhere else in Merseyside, and back boilers almost always qualify for ECO4 replacement funding.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Why St Helens Qualifies Strongly for ECO4</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.75rem;line-height:1.65;">The ECO4 scheme identifies St Helens as a qualifying area, meaning that St Helens households have a stronger baseline eligibility than in areas without this designation. On top of this, qualifying benefits, household income below £31,000 and EPC ratings of D or below all independently trigger eligibility. St Helens has a high proportion of older properties with poor EPC ratings, and a significant number of households on qualifying benefits. These factors combine to make ECO4 funding available to a larger proportion of St Helens households than in many other Merseyside boroughs. We check your eligibility at every free survey at no cost.</p>
          <div style="background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:0.75rem 1rem;">
            <p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:#15803d;margin:0;font-weight:600;">If you or anyone in your household receives Universal Credit, Pension Credit, Child Tax Credit, Income Support or any other qualifying benefit, you may qualify for a fully or partially funded central heating upgrade. We assess this at your free survey.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Back Boilers in St Helens Almost Always Qualify for ECO4 Replacement</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Back boilers are classified as inefficient non-condensing appliances under ECO4 guidelines. This means they almost always qualify for ECO4 replacement funding, regardless of household income or benefit status, because of the EPC improvement that replacing them creates. Many WA10 and WA9 terraces with back boilers qualify for a full central heating upgrade through ECO4, back boiler and fire removed, new combi or system boiler installed in a new location, full new pipework and radiators, all either partially or fully funded. The first-time central heating grant under ECO4 covers exactly this scenario. We assess your specific eligibility at the free survey and advise on what funding is available before any work begins.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">What Back Boiler Replacement in St Helens Actually Involves</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">A back boiler replacement is not a straightforward boiler swap. The back boiler and the gas fire in front of it are removed as a unit. The chimney breast opening is made good. A new boiler location is identified, which for most WA10 terraces is typically the kitchen or a ground floor cupboard. New gas pipework is run to the new location. New radiators are specified and fitted throughout the property, because the back boiler's pipework rarely runs to the optimal radiator positions. The full system is then commissioned and balanced. This is a larger job than a standard combi swap and takes typically 4 to 5 days. We plan every element at the free survey and provide a written fixed-price quote before any work begins.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


