  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Signs Your St Helens Home Needs a Central Heating Upgrade</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">These are the most common situations reported by St Helens homeowners before calling us.</p>
      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>You still have a back boiler</strong><p>Back boilers are inefficient, difficult to service correctly and no longer produced. They almost always qualify for ECO4 replacement funding. If your WA10 property still runs on a back boiler, a funded upgrade to a modern combi is very likely available. Book a free survey and we will assess your eligibility before you commit to anything.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>No central heating in your property</strong><p>If your St Helens property has electric heaters and no gas central heating, you may qualify for a first-time central heating grant under ECO4. This covers the full installation of a gas central heating system including boiler, pipework, radiators and controls for eligible households.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Rooms always cold despite heating on</strong><p>Missing radiators, an undersized back boiler or a poorly balanced system means the heating can never keep up. A free survey identifies whether a radiator addition or a full system upgrade is the right solution.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>EPC rating of D, E, F or G</strong><p>A poor EPC rating is one of the key triggers for ECO4 eligibility. A new central heating installation is the single most impactful EPC improvement available. If your property has an EPC rating of D or below, your eligibility for funded work is strong.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Heating bills very high with poor results</strong><p>Back boilers run at efficiencies well below modern condensing boilers. Replacing a back boiler with an A-rated combi typically reduces gas consumption by 20 to 40%, with higher savings for older, less efficient units.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Cold spots on radiators that bleeding does not fix</strong><p>Persistent cold spots on multiple radiators in a back boiler system indicate magnetite build-up in the system pipework. A power flush before any new components are connected is essential in these cases.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


