      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does central heating installation cost in St Helens?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A full central heating installation in St Helens starts from £3,500. System upgrades start from £1,500. A single radiator addition costs from £200. ECO4 grant funding may reduce or eliminate these costs for eligible St Helens households. We assess eligibility at the free survey at no cost. All prices confirmed in a written fixed-price quote after the site visit.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">ECO4</span>&nbsp; Can ECO4 fund my central heating installation in St Helens?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Very possibly. St Helens is identified as an ECO4 priority area. Households on qualifying benefits including Universal Credit, Pension Credit and Child Tax Credit, households with income below £31,000 and properties with EPC ratings of D or below may all qualify. Back boilers in St Helens almost always qualify for ECO4 replacement funding because of the EPC improvement that replacement creates. We assess your eligibility at the free survey at no cost and advise before you commit to any spend.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">BACK BOILER</span>&nbsp; Do you replace back boilers in St Helens?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Back boiler replacement is one of our most common jobs in St Helens. We remove the back boiler and gas fire, make good the chimney breast opening, position the new boiler in the optimal location for the property, run new pipework and fit a full set of new radiators. Most back boiler replacement jobs take 4 to 5 days. Back boilers almost always qualify for ECO4 replacement funding, which can significantly reduce the cost.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">FIRST TIME</span>&nbsp; My St Helens property has no central heating. Can I get a grant?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes, if you meet the eligibility criteria. The first-time central heating grant under ECO4 covers the full installation of a gas central heating system including boiler, pipework, radiators and controls for eligible households. This is available for properties with an existing gas supply that have not previously had gas central heating. We assess your eligibility at the free survey at no cost.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for St Helens central heating installation?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All central heating installations in St Helens are carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe registered engineers. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
